<p>I followed the Google's guide for Sign-in button at <a href="https://developers.google.com/identity/sign-in/web/backend-auth" rel="nofollow">https://developers.google.com/identity/sign-in/web/backend-auth</a>. After successful sign-in in the browser, I get the id_token:</p>  <pre><code>var id_token = googleUser.getAuthResponse().id_token; </code></pre>  <p>and send it to the server, as instructed. There I'm able to verify it and get the payload:</p>  <pre><code>GoogleIdToken idToken = tokenVerifier.verify(googleIdTokenString);  if (idToken != null) {   return idToken.getPayload(); } </code></pre>  <p>However, I have no clue how to get the user's profile from either the token or the payload.</p>